    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A narrative-driven, single-page scrolling application. The structure flows from Problem (The Crisis) -> Solution (Digital Transition) -> Implementation (Action Plan) -> Key Player (Junctionmed's Vision) -> Future Outlook. This narrative structure is more engaging and persuasive for a user than a simple chapter-by-chapter replication of the report. A sticky navigation bar allows for both guided exploration via scrolling and direct access to specific topics, enhancing usability. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 1. Aging Population (Report Ch.2) -> Goal: Change -> Viz: Line Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Hover tooltips -> Justification: Clearly shows the accelerating trend over time. 2. Digital Transition Sentiment (Ch.3) -> Goal: Compare -> Viz: Mirrored Bar Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Buttons to filter data (Opportunities/Barriers) -> Justification: Visually contrasts the positive and negative perceptions from the field, making the data interactive and explorable. 3. Collaborative Model (Ch.4) -> Goal: Organize -> Viz: HTML/CSS Flowchart -> Interaction: None (static for clarity) -> Justification: A simple, clear visual representation of the process is more effective than a complex interactive one for this concept. 4. Junctionmed Roadmap (Ch.6) -> Goal: Organize/Change -> Viz: HTML/CSS Vertical Timeline -> Interaction: Click to expand details -> Justification: Presents a large amount of information in a compact, user-driven way, keeping the initial view uncluttered. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
